This is the content of my 'help' file on the RPI:

AlRadio Help
============

install dirs
------------

code is all under /var/www/radio

check services like this
------------------------

sudo /etc/init.d/fmradio.sh start
sudo /etc/init.d/fmradio.sh status
sudo /etc/init.d/fmradio.sh stop

sudo /etc/init.d/playserver.sh start
sudo /etc/init.d/playserver.sh status
sudo /etc/init.d/playserver.sh stop

technologies
------------

AlRadio relies on:

* nginx (web server, serves up the Client app)
* si4703 python script (fm radio controller)
* play framework (web services)
* vlc
* streamripper
* alsa

startup scripts
---------------

* startup scripts are in /etc/init.d
* links to these scripts are under /etc/rc?.d
* got the scripts from this url:
  http://blog.scphillips.com/2013/07/getting-a-python-script-to-run-in-the-background-as-a-service-on-boot/


